Note:
Runa Standard Library: Site Module

Provides site-specific configuration and runtime environment management, supporting user/site directories,
platform detection, resource paths, environment overrides, and AI/agent-friendly interfaces.

Features:
- User and site configuration directories
- Platform and environment detection
- Resource and data file location
- Environment variable overrides
- Site-wide hooks and initialization
- Error handling and edge cases
- AI/agent-friendly interfaces
:End Note

Note: Core Types and Constants
Type SiteInfo is Dictionary with:
    user_config_dir as String
    site_config_dir as String
    user_data_dir as String
    site_data_dir as String
    user_cache_dir as String
    site_cache_dir as String
    platform as String
    python_version as Optional[String]
    runa_version as Optional[String]
    environment as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type SiteOptions is Dictionary with:
    env_prefix as Optional[String]
    ai_mode as Boolean defaults to false

Type SiteResult is:
    | SiteSuccess with info as SiteInfo
    | SiteError with message as String and code as String

Note: Core Site Functions
Process called "get_site_info" that takes options as SiteOptions returns SiteResult:
    Note: Implementation detects site/user directories and environment
    Return SiteError with message as "Not implemented" and code as "NOT_IMPLEMENTED"

Process called "get_user_config_dir" returns String:
    Note: Implementation returns user config directory
    Return "~/.config/runa"

Process called "get_site_config_dir" returns String:
    Note: Implementation returns site config directory
    Return "/etc/runa"

Process called "get_user_data_dir" returns String:
    Note: Implementation returns user data directory
    Return "~/.local/share/runa"

Process called "get_site_data_dir" returns String:
    Note: Implementation returns site data directory
    Return "/usr/local/share/runa"

Process called "get_user_cache_dir" returns String:
    Note: Implementation returns user cache directory
    Return "~/.cache/runa"

Process called "get_site_cache_dir" returns String:
    Note: Implementation returns site cache directory
    Return "/var/cache/runa"

Process called "get_platform" returns String:
    Note: Implementation returns platform string
    Return "linux"

Process called "get_python_version" returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Implementation returns Python version if available
    Return None

Process called "get_runa_version" returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Implementation returns Runa version if available
    Return None

Process called "get_environment" returns String:
    Note: Implementation returns environment ("development", "production", etc.)
    Return "development"

Process called "find_resource" that takes name as String and options as SiteOptions returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Implementation locates resource file
    Return None

Process called "set_site_hook" that takes hook as Process returns None:
    Note: Implementation sets site-wide initialization hook
    Return None

Process called "create_site_options" returns SiteOptions:
    Return SiteOptions with:
        env_prefix as None
        ai_mode as false

Process called "Some" that takes value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Implementation depends on core optional types
    Return None

Process called "None" returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Implementation depends on core optional types
    Return None 